CTF Writeup: File Run 1
picoCTF | General Skills Challenge


-----------------------------------------------------------
WHAT WAS THIS CHALLENGE?
-----------------------------------------------------------

A binary executable file was provided. The goal was simply to run it and get the flag. The catch is that downloaded files on Linux are not executable by default. You have to give them permission to run first.


-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 - Download the File
-----------------------------------------------------------

Command used: wget [file URL]

What happened:
wget downloaded the binary file into the current directory. After this, ls confirmed the file was there.

Remember: wget URL downloads any file from the internet straight into your terminal.


-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 - Make the File Executable
-----------------------------------------------------------

Command used: chmod +x run

What happened:
By default, files downloaded from the internet are not allowed to execute on Linux. chmod is the command that changes file permissions. The +x flag adds execute permission, telling Linux that this file is allowed to be run as a program.

Without this step, trying to run the file would give a permission denied error.

Remember: chmod +x filename makes any file executable. You need this before running downloaded programs.


-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 - Run the File
-----------------------------------------------------------

Command used: ./run

What happened:
The ./ tells Linux to run the file from the current directory. Without it, Linux would look for the command in its system paths and not find it. The program ran and printed the flag directly.

Remember: ./filename runs an executable that is in your current directory.


-----------------------------------------------------------
QUICK REFERENCE
-----------------------------------------------------------

wget URL          Download a file from the internet
chmod +x run      Give the file permission to execute
./run             Run the file from the current directory


