-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

Linux does not let you run files by default. This is a security feature. You have to explicitly give a file execute permission using chmod +x before it can run.

The ./ before a filename means run this file from here. You will use this constantly when running programs in CTF challenges.

Some challenges are simple on purpose. The lesson here is not the flag itself but learning the workflow of downloading, permissioning, and running executables in Linux.
